# The upstream dump: ~70 MB gzipped, ~730 MB unpacked. Fetched by `npm run dump`.
.cache/
*.sql
*.sql.bak

# The dictionary is GENERATED, and deliberately not committed. `npm run dict:all` rebuilds it
# byte-for-byte from the public dump pinned in data/PROVENANCE.json — verified, not hoped for.
#
# Keeping it out of git buys two things. It keeps 3 MB of dense generated text (which re-writes
# almost entirely on every regeneration) out of the history forever. And it keeps the one piece of
# data whose upstream grants us no licence — Речко's stress marks — out of an immutable public
# record: a takedown request would mean deleting a release asset, not rewriting published history.
#
# It ships in the extension zips and is attached to every GitHub release.
data/stress-dict.txt
